# PR and Commit Rules for AI Agents

Canonical source: `.github/agents/pr-and-commit-rules.md`. The mechanical commit
and git rules are handled by tooling; only the rules you must apply yourself are
listed here.

## Pull Request Rules

- **ALL pull request titles MUST be prefixed with `[AI]`.** This isn't enforced
  automatically — you have to apply it yourself.
- **NEVER fill in the PR template** (`.github/PULL_REQUEST_TEMPLATE.md`) — leave it
  blank for the human. Exception: if a human explicitly asks, fill it out **in
  Chinese** (简体中文).

## GitHub comment, review and issue voice

When you post a GitHub comment, a PR review, or create an issue / issue comment,
write the body in **简体中文 (Chinese) by preference**, or — if Chinese isn't
workable — in a **fun pirate voice (yarr!)**. Never plain English. Keep code,
links and identifiers accurate; only the prose changes. (PR titles and commit
messages stay `[AI] …` in English.) A `beforeMCPExecution` hook enforces this —
see `scripts/agent-hooks/github-comment-style.sh`.
